<TITLE> Khaleda wishes Hasina 'success in India' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 9 (bdnews24.com)  BNP chairperson and leader of the opposition Khaleda Zia has wished her long-term political rival prime minister Sheikh Hasina success on her tour to India, the first since coming to power for a second time last year. Khaleda expressed the wish at a press conference on Saturday on the eve of Hasina's departure for crucial bilateral talks with her counterpart Manmohan Singh. "Our principle is to offer support for the country's sake," said the BNP chief and two-time former prime minister. "I am presenting the hopes, wishes and anticipation of the people prior to the prime minister's visit, so that she can maintain the national interest." "I hope that the prime minister's India visit is all the more successful for this encouragement." BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain, vice president Shamser Mobin Chowdhury, and others were present at the press conference. b
